//Page 06 - Osteochondral unit

Finding: Trauma - Osteochondral Fracture//


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 06 -Findings of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Trauma - Osteochondral Fracture' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And multiple selection Localizer is enabled
And 'Hypointense line, interruption corticalis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Curved fracture line' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corticalis impression' checkbox is enabled
And 'Articular surface involvement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fragmentation articular surface' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteochondral fragment' checkbox is enabled

And '1' radio button is enabled
And '2a' radio button is enabled
And '2b' radio button is enabled
And '3' radio button is enabled
And '4' radio button is enabled
And 'Haemarthros' radio button is enabled
And 'Lipohaemarthros' is enabled

When I select all parts on multiple selection Localizer
Then all parts are selected and turn red

When I select 'Osteochondral fragment' checkbox
Then 'Diameter fragment in mm' input field is enabled

When I select '4' radio button
Then 'Detection loose body' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Detection loose body' checkbox
Then 'Media compartment' radio button is enabled
Then 'Lateral  compartment' radio button is enabled
Then 'Femoropatellar compartment' radio button is enabled
